In this article, First Lady Michelle Obama delivers remarks at a ceremony honoring the winners of the 2015 National Medal for Museum and Library Service. She praises the awardees for their innovative programming, technological savvy, and enthusiastic engagement with their communities. She emphasizes the importance of libraries and museums in helping achieve national goals such as education, job creation, and healthy families. Mrs. Obama acknowledges the challenges faced by these institutions, including limited time and funding, but highlights the critical services they provide in keeping people from falling through the cracks. She expresses her pride and gratitude for their work and urges them to continue making a difference. The article concludes with the presentation of the awards and a reception at the White House.